\par
It was fall, and my mom struck a deal with Tony.\par
\par
 \par
\par
"Look, you can keep your job at Martin's. I will give you a roof over your head, food on the table, clothes to wear."\par
\par
 \par
\par
 "K," he said. "And?" \par
\par
  \par
\par
