\par
  \par
\par
"I said, Finish your homework."\par
\par
 \par
\par
"I said I am going to finish it in first hour tomorrow! You cannot tell me what to do. You are not my dad!" \par
\par
 \par
\par
He moved quickly toward me, face still frozen in a scowl. I knew what he wanted to do.\par
\par
  \par
\par
"You can't hit me! You are not allowed to hit me! I'm gonna tell Mommy!"\par
\par
 \par
\par
 He was red with anger and his lips stayed tight. "Do your homework. Now." His voice was louder and meant that he was using every bit of his strength not to hit me. \par
\par
 \par
\par
"I'm taking it into my room!" I grabbed it and ran into my bedroom. I wouldn't let him see me do my homework. I wouldn't let him think I was afraid of him.\par
